==English==
===Etymology 1===
[[Category:Dutch derivations]]
From Middle Dutch ''[[scipper]]'', from ''[[scip]]''. Confer ''[[ship]]''.
====Noun====
{{en-noun|skipper|skippers}}
#(''nautical'') The [[master]] of a [[ship]].
#A [[coach]], [[director]], or other [[leader]].
#{{cricket}} the [[captain]] of a [[cricket]] [[team]].
====Verb====
{{en-verb|skipper|skippers|skippered|skippering}}
#{{transitive}} To be the skipper of a ship

